SIMPLE: incongruity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incongruity
<hw>In`con*gru"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Incongruities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets>
not + <ets>congruity</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>incongruit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being incongruous; lack of
congruity; unsuitableness; inconsistency; impropriety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fathers make use of this acknowledgment of the
<qex>incongruity</qex> of images to the Deity, from thence to prove the
<qex>incongruity</qex> of the worship of them.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disagreement of parts; lack of symmetry or of
harmony.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is incongruous; lack of
congruity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incongruous</ent>⟦br⟧
